snippet.textDisplay:
Wanwun part in that song of coke studio will only give goosebumps to those kashmir's, who are either alien to the kashmiri culture or have never attended a kashmiri marriage function.
Wanwun is the part and parcel of our marriages in fact of  every celebration. their is absolutely nothing new about it.
Next time when you attend the marriage function of your near and dear ones. Please do listen keenly to what our resilient women are singing..their is a very deep meaning to what they sing and they aren't their just to waste their precious time.
Preserve your culture in practical life and not only in coke studios only.

snippet.textDisplay:
Each time I listen to this Song, I am swept away by its enchanting beauty, and my heart is filled with an indescribable longing. The soul-stirring music and poignant lyrics evoke emotions that resonate within me, drawing me back to this song again and again.
I am utterly captivated by the profound emotions and enchanting words of this Kashmiri Song. The way you beautifully blend the essence of our rich Kashmiri culture with the soul-stirring music is truly remarkable.
I want to extend my heartfelt gratitude to the talented artists, Aashima Mahajan, Alif, and Noor Mohammad, hailing from the valley, for their exceptional performances. Their heartfelt rendition has not only preserved the authenticity of our Kashmiri heritage but has also brought it to life, touching the hearts of countless listeners.
Coke Studio's collaboration with these remarkable artists has not only showcased their immense talent but has also given a platform to the voices of our valley. Through their captivating performances, they have become ambassadors of our culture, sharing its beauty and soul with the world.
Thank you, Coke Studio, for embracing and showcasing the talents of our local artists, and for allowing the melodies of our valley to resonate across boundaries. ❤❤
